- Your own UI/UX.
- Possibility to use it in your personal projects, IDEs, or company tools.

---

## ðŸ§  Basics You Should Know Before Building

Before diving into building your own AI code assistant, itâ€™s important to understand the foundational technologies that make this project come to life. Here are the core concepts you'll need:

- **React.js** â€“ For rendering and managing your frontend UI. You'll use React to create an interactive, real-time Monaco Editor component, manage state, and respond to user inputs like code changes.
  - **Key Concepts:** Components, useState, useEffect, JSX
  - **Why itâ€™s Important:** React lets you efficiently manage UI updates in response to user interactions with Monaco, ensuring smooth user experience with real-time code suggestions.

  ![React Logo](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a7/React-icon.svg)

- **Monaco Editor** â€“ This is the powerful code editor used in VSCode. Itâ€™s customizable, lightweight, and perfect for embedding into web applications.
  - **Key Concepts:** Monaco Editor API, syntax highlighting, decorators, and code completion features.
  - **Why itâ€™s Important:** Monaco lets you embed a highly interactive code editor with language support, autocompletion, and syntax highlighting, which is essential for a code suggestion tool like this.

  ![Monaco Editor](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Monaco_Editor_Logo.svg/512px-Monaco_Editor_Logo.svg.png)

- **OpenAI API** â€“ This is where the magic happens. The OpenAI GPT-4 model generates code suggestions based on the code context you provide. Understanding how to send API requests and handle responses is crucial.
  - **Key Concepts:** API requests, POST methods, API keys, JSON response handling
  - **Why itâ€™s Important:** This is the core of the AI assistantâ€”learning how to use the OpenAI API to generate code suggestions and work with the responses in your app is essential.

  ![OpenAI Logo](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/OpenAI.png/640px-OpenAI.png)

- **Node.js + Express** â€“ These will be used for creating the backend server that handles the API requests to OpenAI. The server will ensure secure communication between your frontend and OpenAI.
  - **Key Concepts:** Express routes, request/response cycle, middleware, environment variables
  - **Why itâ€™s Important:** A backend is needed to securely store your OpenAI API keys and handle requests from the frontend, without exposing sensitive data in the browser.

  ![Node.js Logo](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Node.js_logo_2015.svg/640px-Node.js_logo_2015.svg.png)

- **Async/Await & JSON** â€“ JavaScript's asynchronous programming is critical when working with API calls, especially when fetching data from OpenAI. Understanding async/await and how to work with JSON will make your development process smoother.

  ![Async Await](https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*V6jFWllv3RNVlOTFnS_j8Q.png)

