## ðŸ› ï¸ Code Implementation (JS-Friendly Format)

### ðŸ“¦ Step 1: Install Monaco Editor

```bash
npm install monaco-editor react-monaco-editor
```

### ðŸ’» Step 2: Setup the Editor in React

```jsx
import MonacoEditor from 'react-monaco-editor';

const Editor = ({ code, setCode }) => (
  <MonacoEditor
    height="500"
    defaultLanguage="javascript"
    value={code}
    onChange={setCode}
    theme="vs-dark"
  />
);
```

### ðŸ”Œ Step 3: Backend API to Fetch Suggestions

```js
// server/suggest.js (Express route)
const express = require("express");
const router = express.Router();
const { Configuration, OpenAIApi } = require("openai");

const configuration = new Configuration({ apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY });
const openai = new OpenAIApi(configuration);

router.post("/", async (req, res) => {
  const { code } = req.body;
  const prompt = `Suggest the next line for this code:\n${code}`;

  try {
    const response = await openai.createChatCompletion({
      model: "gpt-4",
      messages: [{ role: "user", content: prompt }],
    });

    const suggestion = response.data.choices[0].message.content;
    res.json({ suggestion });
  } catch (err) {
    res.status(500).json({ error: "Failed to fetch suggestion" });
  }
});

module.exports = router;
```

### ðŸŒ Step 4: Frontend â€” Send Code and Show Suggestions

```js
const getSuggestion = async (code) => {
  const res = await fetch("/api/suggest", {
    method: "POST",
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    body: JSON.stringify({ code })
  });
  const data = await res.json();
  return data.suggestion;
};
```

### âœ¨ Step 5: Inline Suggestion in Monaco (Advanced)

```js
editorRef.current.deltaDecorations([], [
  {
    range: new monaco.Range(line, column, line, column),
    options: {
      after: {
        content: suggestion,
        inlineClassName: "ghost-text"
      }
    }
  }
]);
```

